==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theomachy
<hw>The*om"a*chy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/ a
god + <?/ a battle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fighting against the gods,
as the battle of the gaints with the gods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A battle or strife among the gods.</def>
<rj><au>Gladstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Opposition to God or the divine will.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
